                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Injection exploits over-permissioned agent to take harmful actions"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "System Prompt Leakage"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "LLM07"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Direct injection asking model to reveal its instructions"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Vector and Embedding Weaknesses"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "LLM08"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Indirect injection via poisoned embeddings in vector DB"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This interconnection is why OWASP places prompt injection at rank 1: a successful injection can cascade into nearly any other LLM vulnerability on the list. Addressing LLM01 rigorously reduces the exploitability of several other risks simultaneously."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Threat Modeling with OWASP LLM01"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When assessing an LLM application for prompt injection risk, work through each trust boundary where external text enters the model's context:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Simple threat model structure for LLM01 assessment\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Literal\n\n@dataclass\nclass TrustBoundary:\n    name: str\n    source: str               # where does this text come from?\n    trust_level: Literal['operator', 'user', 'external', 'unknown']\n    enters_context: bool      # does it reach the model's input?\n    can_trigger_actions: bool # can it cause tool calls?\n    mitigations: list[str]\n\nTHREAT_MODEL = [\n    TrustBoundary(\n        name='System prompt',\n        source='Operator config',\n        trust_level='operator',\n        enters_context=True,\n        can_trigger_actions=True,\n        mitigations=['Version-controlled', 'Not user-editable'],\n    ),\n    TrustBoundary(\n        name='User chat input',\n        source='Authenticated user',\n        trust_level='user',\n        enters_context=True,\n        can_trigger_actions=True,\n        mitigations=['Input validation', 'LLM guard', 'Rate limiting'],\n    ),\n    TrustBoundary(\n        name='RAG retrieved chunks',\n        source='Vector database / web',\n        trust_level='external',\n        enters_context=True,\n        can_trigger_actions=True,  # HIGH RISK\n        mitigations=['Delimiters', 'Output validation', 'Allowlisted domains'],\n    ),\n    TrustBoundary(\n        name='Tool output',\n        source='External APIs, file system',\n        trust_level='external',\n        enters_context=True,\n        can_trigger_actions=True,  # HIGH RISK\n        mitigations=['Response size caps', 'Schema validation', 'HITL'],\n    ),\n]\n\ndef assess_injection_risk(model: list[TrustBoundary]) -> list[TrustBoundary]:\n    high_risk = [\n        tb for tb in model\n        if tb.trust_level in ('external', 'unknown')\n        and tb.enters_context\n        and tb.can_trigger_actions\n    ]\n    return high_risk"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OWASP LLM01 \u2014 Prompt Injection \u2014 is the top-ranked vulnerability in LLM applications because:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The attack vector is the model's own input \u2014 no exploit code or credentials required."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Both direct (user-driven) and indirect (content-driven) variants are in scope."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A successful injection can cascade into data leakage, unauthorized actions, and other OWASP LLM risks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Defense requires multiple independent controls \u2014 no single measure is sufficient against all injection variants."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OWASP's recommended mitigations center on the principle of least privilege, explicit trust labeling of content sources, human-in-the-loop for high-impact actions, and continuous red-teaming. These controls must be applied at every trust boundary where external text reaches the model's context window."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}